.Dd April 18, 2026
.Dt PROWLCTL 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm prowlctl
.Nd control utility for prowld(8)
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl \-json
.Ar command
.Op Ar args ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is the command-line interface for
.Xr prowld 8 .
It connects to the
.Xr prowld 8
control socket at
.Pa /var/run/prowld/prowld.sock
and sends commands over the JSON IPC protocol.
Most commands require appropriate privilege;
operations that modify service state or system configuration
must be run as root.
.Pp
The following global option is available:
.Bl -tag -width "--json"
.It Fl \-json
Print raw JSON responses instead of human-readable output.
Useful for scripts and monitoring tools.
.El
.Sh COMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width "reload-config"
.It Cm list Op Fl \-enabled | Fl \-failed | Fl \-type Ns = Ns Ar type
List all known jobs.
With no filter options all loaded jobs are shown regardless of state.
.Fl \-enabled
shows only jobs that are set enabled (via rc.conf or the enable command).
.Fl \-failed
shows only jobs currently in the
.Dv failed
state.
.Fl \-type Ns = Ns Ar type
filters by job type; valid values are
.Cm daemon ,
.Cm oneshot ,
.Cm timer ,
.Cm socket ,
and
.Cm rcshim .
.It Cm status Ar label
Show detailed status for a single job, including its state, PID,
restart count, last exit code, and any status message reported via
sd_notify
.Pq Dv STATUS=... .
.Ar label
may be either the full unit label
.Pq e.g., Dq org.midnightbsd.sshd
or the short rc_name
.Pq e.g., Dq sshd .
.It Cm start Ar label
Start the named job.
The job must be loaded and not currently running.
If the job has unsatisfied hard dependencies the command will fail.
.It Cm stop Ar label
Stop the named job.
.Xr prowld 8
sends
.Dv SIGTERM
and waits up to
.Va exit_timeout
seconds for the process to exit before sending
.Dv SIGKILL .
.It Cm restart Ar label
Stop then restart the named job.
Equivalent to
.Cm stop
followed by
.Cm start
but performed atomically in the daemon.
.It Cm reload Ar label
Send
.Dv SIGHUP
to the named job.
By convention this causes a daemon to re-read its configuration
without dropping connections.
The job must be in the
.Dv running
state.
.It Cm enable Ar label
Mark a job to start at boot by setting
.Va \*(Lt rc_name \*(Gt _enable=YES
in
.Pa /etc/rc.conf
via
.Xr sysrc 8 .
For unit jobs that do not have an rc_name the job's label is used.
.It Cm disable Ar label
Mark a job to not start at boot by setting
.Va \*(Lt rc_name \*(Gt _enable=NO
in
.Pa /etc/rc.conf .
Does not stop a currently running instance.
.It Cm mask Ar label
Unconditionally prevent a job from starting even as a dependency.
Creates a placeholder file in
.Pa /var/db/prowld/masked.d/ .
A masked job cannot be started with
.Cm start
until it is unmasked.
.It Cm unmask Ar label
Remove a mask created by
.Cm mask .
The job must then be explicitly enabled or started if desired.
.It Cm show Ar label
Dump the effective configuration of a job as a JSON object.
The output reflects all parsed unit-file fields and runtime defaults.
Useful for verifying that a unit file was parsed correctly.
.It Cm reload-config
Rescan all unit directories and
.Xr rc.d 8
script directories for new or changed files,
then rebuild the dependency graph.
Running jobs are not stopped or restarted.
Equivalent to sending
.Dv SIGHUP
to
.Xr prowld 8
directly.
.It Cm daemon-reexec
Re-execute
.Xr prowld 8
in place without disturbing running services.
Intended for upgrading the daemon binary while the system is live.
The new process inherits all open file descriptors and job state.
.It Cm dependencies Ar label
Show the dependency list for a job.
Each entry names the dependency and whether it is a hard
.Pq Cm requires
or soft
.Pq Cm wants
dependency.
.It Cm graph Op Fl \-format Ns = Ns Ar fmt
Emit the full service dependency graph.
Without options, output is a human-readable edge table showing
each job and its direct dependencies.
With
.Fl \-format Ns = Ns Ar dot ,
output is Graphviz DOT format suitable for rendering with
.Xr dot 1 .
.It Cm logs Ar label Op Fl \-follow Op Fl \-lines Ns = Ns Ar N
Display the captured log output for a job.
Only available for jobs that write stdout or stderr to
.Pa /var/log/prowld/jobs/ Ns Ar label Ns Pa .log .
.Pp
.Fl \-follow
tails the file continuously, similar to
.Xr tail 1
.Fl f .
Use
.Ic ^C
to stop following.
.Fl \-lines Ns = Ns Ar N
limits initial output to the last
.Ar N
lines; the default is 50.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Pp
Additional exit codes:
.Bl -tag -width "3" -compact
.It 1
Job not found or invalid label.
.It 2
Job is in a failed state and the operation could not be performed.
.It 3
Operation not permitted (insufficient privilege).
.It 4
.Xr prowld 8
is not running or not responding on the control socket.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
List all loaded services:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
prowlctl list
.Ed
.Pp
Show only failed services:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
prowlctl list --failed
.Ed
.Pp
Start the SSH daemon:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
prowlctl start org.midnightbsd.sshd
.Ed
.Pp
Enable a service at boot:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
prowlctl enable sshd
.Ed
.Pp
Check detailed status, using short rc name:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
prowlctl status sshd
.Ed
.Pp
Follow a service's log output:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
prowlctl logs org.midnightbsd.nginx --follow
.Ed
.Pp
Render the dependency graph as a PDF:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
prowlctl graph --format=dot | dot -Tpdf -o deps.pdf
.Ed
.Pp
Get machine-readable status for scripting:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
prowlctl --json status org.midnightbsd.sshd | jq .state
.Ed
.Pp
Mask a unit to prevent it from ever starting:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
prowlctl mask org.midnightbsd.bluetooth
.Ed
.Sh DIAGNOSTICS
.Bl -diag
.It "prowld not running or socket unavailable"
.Xr prowld 8
is not started, or the control socket at
.Pa /var/run/prowld/prowld.sock
does not exist.
Start prowld or check
.Pa /var/log/prowld/prowld.log
for startup errors.
If prowld was started with a custom run directory via
.Fl s ,
the socket will be under that directory instead.
.It "operation not permitted"
The command requires root privilege.
Re-run with
.Xr su 1
or
.Xr sudo 8 .
.It "job not found: \*(Ltlabel\*(Gt"
No loaded job matches the given label or rc_name.
Run
.Cm prowlctl list
to see all known jobs and confirm the spelling.
If the unit file was recently added, run
.Cm prowlctl reload-config
first.
.It "job is masked"
The job has been masked with
.Cm prowlctl mask
and cannot be started.
Use
.Cm prowlctl unmask Ar label
to remove the mask.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "/var/log/prowld/jobs/<label>.log" -compact
.It Pa /var/run/prowld/prowld.sock
.Xr prowld 8
control socket.
If prowld was started with
.Fl s Ar rundir ,
the socket is at
.Pa Ar rundir Ns /prowld.sock
instead.
.It Pa /var/db/prowld/masked.d/
Directory of mask files created by
.Cm prowlctl mask .
.It Pa /var/log/prowld/jobs/ Ns Ar label Ns Pa .log
Per-job log file, read by
.Cm prowlctl logs .
.It Pa /etc/rc.conf
Modified by
.Cm enable
and
.Cm disable
via
.Xr sysrc 8 .
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr sysrc 8 ,
.Xr service 8 ,
.Xr rc 8 ,
.Xr prowld 8 ,
.Xr tail 1 ,
.Xr dot 1
.Sh HISTORY
.Nm
first appeared in MidnightBSD 4.1.
